 These RRTMG files are validated.
 30 bands: 1-14 for SW, 15-30 for LW.

 BC: black carbon
 BRC:brown carbon 
 DU: dust
 NI: nitrate
 OC: organic carbon
 SS: sea salt
 SU: sulfate

 Need to calculate: optical depth, single scattering albedo, asymmetry factor
 bext: mass extinction efficiency m2/kg  [radius, relative humidity, lambda] 
 g: asymmetry factor                     [radius, relative humidity, lambda]
 bsca: mass scattering efficiency m2/kg  [radius, relative humidity, lambda]

 optical_depth = delta_p/9.8 * bext
 single scattering albedo = bsca/bext

 2-D interpolation: linit2 
